news.title: Aqua Line's Greater Noida Extension gets public investment board nod
news.para: This is the first of the two proposed extensions of the Aqua Line, the other being the expressway arm from Sector 142 to Botanical Garden, whose alignment and other aspects are yet to be finalised.

news.title: Chandigarh: To raise IT Park housing project, CHB to go to centre again
news.para: “All the projects are approved in the Chandigarh Master Plan-2031. They follow the notification of the ESZ and other wildlife norms. The site is located 1.25 km away from the ESZ. In fact, it is around 1.56 km away,” an official claimed.

news.title: Colonies in Hubballi crippled, lack basic facilities
news.para: The areas are on Kusugal Road, about 5 km from the city centre, and were planned out about 20 years ago. Nearly 4,000 families live in this area and are deprived of basic facilities.

news.title: Visakhapatnam development body slashes plot prices to woo public
news.para: A state-level committee fixed ₹18,000 per square yard price for the sale of 446 plots in the layout being developed by the Visakhapatnam Metropolitan Region Development Authority (VMRDA) in Palavalasa village near Anandapuram in Vizag suburbs.

news.title: Chandigarh administration's review meeting on master plan 2031 on Dec 13
news.para: Even after almost seven years of coming up with the master plan, most projects remain only on paper. Making them a reality is the challenging task for the authorities.

news.title: Gurugram: Flats not handed over, Supertech Basera buyers say 'no option but to protest'
news.para: The affordable housing project was launched in 2015 and the buyers were promised possession by 2020. However, till date the developer has offered possession of only two towers partly, while the rest of the 13 towers are only 50% constructed.

news.title: Gurugram deputy commissioner to meet RWAs to discuss structural audit report
news.para: The audit report, based on visual checks conducted by four agencies, was submitted to the committee headed by additional deputy commissioner Vishram Kumar Meena around three weeks ago.

news.title: M3M India buys 1.3-acre land in Gurugram for Rs 200 crore
news.para: The land, located near IFFCO Chowk, has been acquired through an auction conducted by Haryana Shahari Vikas Pradhikaran (HSVP).

news.title: NGT forms panel for report on green norm violations by housing project in Ghaziabad
news.para: The green panel was hearing a petition alleging the Siddharth Vihar Yojana in Ghaziabad, a scheme or project by the Awas Vikas Parishad, was being developed through several builders in violation of environmental norms.

news.title: Greater Noida: La Residentia residents launch poster protest against builder
news.para: Residents maintained that the project launched with great fanfare in 2009 with the tagline ‘Luxury within reach’ is far from what was promised as lack of maintenance, incomplete towers and no registry are some of the issues plaguing the residents.

news.title: Prime minister inaugurates phase-I of Nagpur Metro rail project
news.para: Prime minister also laid the foundation stone of Phase-II of the metro project. Phase-II of the project will be developed at more than Rs 6,700 crore. It will have 32 stations and cover a distance of 43.8 km, they said.

news.title: Ayodhya master plan 2031 approved by Uttar Pradesh CM
news.para: In the works for the past two years, the master plan 2031 was put up by the housing and urban planning department on the CM's table this week after disposing of 1,084 objections that were raised by the citizens.

news.title: Pune civic body to promote private town planning schemes
news.para: As per the PMC's plan, private players should have at least 50 acres of land. Of the total land, 60% would be used for development and the remaining 40% would be reserved for amenities.

news.title: Gujarat mulls incentivizing grey water treatment plants in residential projects
news.para: Usually, grey water constitutes wastewater from bathtubs, showers, bathroom washbasins, washing machines, sinks, and laundry tubs. It does not include toilet discharge water.

news.title: No regularization of illegal construction in Gujarat government schemes
news.para: In its 2011 avatar, the impact fee law did not permit such regularization either unless an NOC was procured from the board. The AMC clarified that there is no provision in the ordinance to regularize illegal constructions in GHB colonies.
